          "id": "semaa-policy-001::0",
          "index": 0,
          "content": "SEMAA Marine Safety Policy v1.0\n\nOrganization: SEMAA Marine Operations\nEffective Date: 2026-01-15\nOwner: Marine Compliance Team\n\nSection 1. Vessel Classes\n- Class A vessels: coastal survey boats under 40 meters.\n- Class B vessels: offshore support vessels over 40 meters.\n\nSection 2. Inspection Cadence\n- Class A vessels must complete a full inspection every 30 days.\n- Class B vessels must complete a full inspection every 14 days.\n- Emergency inspection is mandatory within 24 hours after any engine overheating event.\n\nSection 3. Critical Contacts\n- Safety Director: Alice Chen\n- Fleet Manager: Brian Wu\n- Incident Hotline: +886-2-5555-1200\n\nSection 4. Fuel Handling\n- Diesel transfer requires two-person confirmation.\n- Maximum transfer window is 90 minutes.\n- Any transfer over 70 minutes must be annotated in transfer log.\n\nSection 5. Non-Compliance Actions\n- First violation: written warning and corrective training within 7 days.\n- Second violation: temporary vessel suspension up to 72 hours.\n- Third violation: escalation to executive compliance board.",
