          "id": "semaa-incident-003::0",
          "index": 0,
          "content": "SEMAA Incident Report IR-2026-003\n\nReported By: Captain Henry Lin\nDate: 2026-02-03\nVessel: Aurora-17\nVessel Class: Class A\nRoute: Keelung to Hualien\n\nSummary\nAt 14:20 local time, the main engine temperature exceeded threshold and triggered an overheating alert.\nThe vessel reduced speed and returned to nearest safe harbor.\n\nTimeline\n- 14:20 Alert triggered by engine monitoring system.\n- 14:27 Chief engineer initiated cooling protocol.\n- 14:41 Temperature normalized.\n- 15:10 Vessel docked at Keelung auxiliary pier.\n\nActions Taken\n- Emergency inspection request submitted at 15:25.\n- Inspection completed at 19:30 on the same day.\n- Fuel transfer operation postponed to next day.\n\nFindings\n- Cooling pump filter blockage was the direct cause.\n- Last full inspection date was 2026-01-08.\n- Required 30-day class inspection was still within valid period.\n\nAssigned Follow-ups\n- Fleet Manager Brian Wu to verify spare filter inventory by 2026-02-05.\n- Safety Director Alice Chen to review emergency response drill cadence.",
