          "content": "SEMAA Crew Training Record TR-2026-Q1\n\nProgram: Emergency Response and Fuel Transfer Safety\nCoordinator: Alice Chen\nQuarter: 2026 Q1\n\nTraining Modules\n- Module A: Engine overheating response protocol.\n- Module B: Two-person diesel transfer verification.\n- Module C: Incident communication escalation.\n\nAttendance\n- Vessel Aurora-17: 12 attendees, completion rate 100 percent.\n- Vessel Meridian-22: 9 attendees, completion rate 89 percent.\n- Vessel Orion-09: 11 attendees, completion rate 100 percent.\n\nAssessment Scores\n- Aurora-17 average score: 92.\n- Meridian-22 average score: 84.\n- Orion-09 average score: 90.\n\nAction Items\n- Meridian-22 requires remedial drill by 2026-03-05.\n- All captains must submit updated emergency contact trees by 2026-03-10.\n\nCompliance Notes\n- Minimum passing score is 80.\n- Any vessel below 90 percent completion must schedule makeup training within 14 days.",
