          "content": "SEMAA Budget and Procurement Plan BP-2026-H1\n\nDepartment: Marine Operations and Safety\nPrepared By: Finance Lead Irene Kuo\nPeriod: 2026-01-01 to 2026-06-30\n\nBudget Allocation\n- Safety training budget: USD 120,000.\n- Spare parts budget: USD 340,000.\n- Emergency response reserve: USD 80,000.\n\nProcurement Priorities\n- Priority 1: Cooling pump filters CPF-9, target 1,200 units.\n- Priority 2: Relay clamps RC-12, target 300 units.\n- Priority 3: Lubricant LT-55, target 1,500 liters.\n\nVendor Strategy\n- Primary vendor for CPF-9: OceanCore Parts Ltd.\n- Secondary vendor for CPF-9: HarborTech Supply Co.\n- Dual-vendor policy required for all critical engine components.\n\nControls and Thresholds\n- Any single PO above USD 50,000 requires dual approval.\n- Emergency reserve usage above USD 20,000 requires Safety Director notification within 12 hours.\n- Monthly variance above 8 percent triggers executive review.\n\nMilestones\n- March checkpoint: complete 45 percent of CPF-9 annual target.\n- June checkpoint: complete 70 percent of CPF-9 annual target.",
